We're in the middle of upgrading to 3.1.1, and when I tested the Activity Stream gadget, I found it had a major impact on the CPU for about a minute.  For now, I've disabled it by disabling the Activity Stream Plugin--we have over 1000 users, and it isn't acceptable for our server to be jammed up for a minute every time someone loads this gadget.

I looked on your website for some inforamtion, and found none.  It looks like anything that was there was removed  (google reports a link to the plugins.atlassian.com, but searching for the plugin there turns up nothing).  The web link from the plugin repository similarly leads to a dead end.  Searching on your doc site turns up a description of the gadget, but nothing else.

This is an important gadget (for Jira dashboards), and we'd like to be able to use it.  I'm told that the initial release of the Jira activity stream gadget had a similar problem that was soon fixed.  Can the same fix be applied for Confluence?  Can we get information on the plans for this feature?

