The basic process for configuring Confluence and JIRA to talk with one another is convoluted at best in our current [Confluence Documentation|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF210/Confluence+and+JIRA].  There's too much going on and the process can be confusing to follow, which seems to be impacting the support load.

We already have a clean-cut process outlined in our [Dragon Slayer docs|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/ATLAS/Dragons+Stage+4+-+Install+Confluence#DragonsStage4-InstallConfluence-Step5.GetJIRAandConfluenceTalking].  Perhaps we can reorganize the official docs and separate the basic hookup process from the rest of the information for clarity's sake.

