This case was created based on a support request from a customer experiencing slowness in site searching:

{quote}

I do performance tests, because it takes about 8 -12 before I get a search result on dosearchsite.action.

Requisites
- I have cleaned the application caches
- About 670 spaces in the application
- I'm a superuser

First test (see screenshot):
- I send a request "test" for all spaces
- The method DefaultSpaceManager.getPermittedSpacesByType takes 7264ms of about 12000ms.
- The sql statement to get the data takes 6ms

Second test (see screenshot):
- I send the same request
- The method DefaultSpaceManager.getPermittedSpacesByType takes 5224ms
- The method DefaultSpaceManager.getSpacesByType takes 327ms
=> If the complete method takes 5224ms and one method takes 327ms then it's obvious that sorting the collection takes the rest of time.

{code}
public List getPermittedSpacesByType(User user, SpaceType type)
    {
        List permittedSpacesForUser;

        if (userAccessor.isSuperUser(user))
            permittedSpacesForUser = getSpacesByType(type);
        else
// Never called. I'm superuser

        Collections.sort(permittedSpacesForUser, new SpaceComparator());

        return permittedSpacesForUser;
    }
    
{code}

If you have a look at the sql of the first screenshot, you will notice that the result is sorted by space name. Takes 6ms.

Sorting the collection by name and then by key, if the name is equals takes ~4,9 seconds.

Isn't it better to get the result sorted by name and key from the database?
{quote}

